s exceptional.\", \"from\": 795, \"to\": 894, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Those three things\", \"from\": 795, \"to\": 813}, {\"ngram\": \"one rider\", \"from\": 840, \"to\": 849}, {\"ngram\": \"one summer\", \"from\": 853, \"to\": 863}, {\"ngram\": \"Evenepoel\", \"from\": 869, \"to\": 878}]}, {\"sentence\": \"With 30km to go, the Belgian decided he'd had enough of waiting and blasted off into the distance leaving world-class riders including his main rival, Mathieu van der Poel, behind.\", \"from\": 896, \"to\": 1076, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 917, \"end\": 924, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"score\": 0.9972631080383573, \"rank\": 0.0027443718547404163, \"text\": \"Belgian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Belgium\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"30km\", \"from\": 901, \"to\": 905}, {\"ngram\": \"the distance\", \"from\": 981, \"to\": 993}, {\"ngram\": \"world-class riders\", \"from\": 1002, \"to\": 1020}, {\"ngram\": \"his main rival\", \"from\": 1031, \"to\": 1045}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He sped up to the breakaway leaders and rode through them, dropping them one by one as tried in vain to cling on to his wheel.\", \"from\": 1077, \"to\": 1203, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the breakaway leaders\", \"from\": 1091, \"to\": 1112}, {\"ngram\": \"vain\", \"from\": 1173, \"to\": 1177}, {\"ngram\": \"his wheel\", \"from\": 1193, \"to\": 1202}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It had been a tactical road race; Evenepoel turned it into a 45-minute time-trial, knowing no one could live with him.\", \"from\": 1204, \"to\": 1322, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a tactical road race\", \"from\": 1216, \"to\": 1236}, {\"ngram\": \"Evenepoel\", \"from\": 1238, \"to\": 1247}, {\"ngram\": \"a 45-minute time-trial\", \"from\": 1263, \"to\": 1285}, {\"ngram\": \"no one\", \"from\": 1295, \"to\": 1301}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There was some late drama when his rear tyre punctured with 3km to go.\", \"from\": 1324, \"to\": 1394, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"some late drama\", \"from\": 1334, \"to\": 1349}, {\"ngram\": \"his rear tyre\", \"from\": 1355, \"to\": 1368}, {\"ngram\": \"3km\", \"from\": 1384, \"to\": 1387}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In an incredible scene, Evenepoel stood on a narrow road next to his busted bike, surrounded by thick waves of fans while he screamed at a mechanic in the distance to hurry up and bring him a new one.\", \"from\": 1395, \"to\": 1595, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an incredible scene\", \"from\": 1398, \"to\": 1417}, {\"ngram\": \"Evenepoel\", \"from\": 1419, \"to\": 1428}, {\"ngram\": \"a narrow road\", \"from\": 1438, \"to\": 1451}, {\"ngram\": \"his busted bike\", \"from\": 1460, \"to\": 1475}, {\"ngram\": \"thick waves\", \"from\": 1491, \"to\": 1502}, {\"ngram\": \"fans\", \"from\": 1506, \"to\": 1510}, {\"ngram\": \"a mechanic\", \"from\": 1532, \"to\": 1542}, {\"ngram\": \"the distance\", \"from\": 1546, \"to\": 1558}, {\"ngram\": \"a new one\", \"from\": 1585, \"to\": 1594}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After what seemed like an eternity, finally it arrived, and he got the message that his lead was still a healthy minute.\", \"from\": 1596, \"to\": 1716, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an eternity\", \"from\": 1619, \"to\": 1630}, {\"ngram\": \"the message\", \"from\": 1663, \"to\": 1674}, {\"ngram\": \"his lead\", \"from\": 1680, \"to\": 1688}, {\"ngram\": \"a healthy minute\", \"from\": 1699, \"to\": 1715}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When he reached the finish line he hopped off his bike and threw his arms out wide.\", \"from\": 1718, \"to\": 1801, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the finish line\", \"from\": 1734, \"to\": 1749}, {\"ngram\": \"his bike\", \"from\": 1764, \"to\": 1772}, {\"ngram\": \"his arms\", \"from\": 1783, \"to\": 1791}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Standing under the Eiffel Tower, it will be one of the iconic images that endures long after his remarkable career is over.\", \"from\": 1802, \"to\": 1925, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Eiffel Tower\", \"from\": 1817, \"to\": 1833}, {\"ngram\": \"the iconic images\", \"from\": 1853, \"to\": 1870}, {\"ngram\": \"his remarkable career\", \"from\": 1895, \"to\": 1916}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was a symbol of his dominance; the Eiffel Tower could have laid down on its side and still not touched his nearest rival.\", \"from\": 1926, \"to\": 2050, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a symbol\", \"from\": 1933, \"to\": 1941}, {\"ngram\": \"his dominance\", \"from\": 1945, \"to\": 1958}, {\"ngram\": \"the Eiffel Tower\", \"from\": 1960, \"to\": 1976}, {\"ngram\": \"its side\", \"from\": 2001, \"to\": 2009}, {\"ngram\": \"his nearest rival\", \"from\": 2032, \"to\": 2049}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Behind him, France secured an unlikely double in Valentin Madouas and Christophe Laporte.\", \"from\": 2052, \"to\": 2141, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2064, \"end\": 2070, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.9767478196709908, \"rank\": 0.015283013564636294, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_rugby_union_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2101, \"end\": 2117, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valentin_Madouas\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Valentin Madouas\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valentin_Madouas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valentin_Madouas\"}, {\"begin\": 2122, \"end\": 2140, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christophe_Laporte\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Christophe Laporte\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christophe_Laporte\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christophe_Laporte\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an unlikely double\", \"from\": 2079, \"to\": 2097}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Madouas, the French national road race champion, had clung on gamely as Evenepoel obliterated the field and he was the last rider to be dropped, with 15km remaining of the Montmartre circuit that staged the finale of the race.\", \"from\": 2142, \"to\": 2368, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2142, \"end\": 2149, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valentin_Madouas\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Madouas\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valentin_Madouas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valentin_Madouas\"}, {\"begin\": 2155, \"end\": 2189, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_National_Road_Race_Championships\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French national road race champion\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_National_Road_Race_Championships\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_National_Road_Race_Championships\"}, {\"begin\": 2314, \"end\": 2324, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montmartre\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.1646832038701217e-14, \"text\": \"Montmartre\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montmartre\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montmartre\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"clung\", \"from\": 2195, \"to\": 2200}, {\"ngram\": \"Evenepoel\", \"from\": 2214, \"to\": 2223}, {\"ngram\": \"the field\", \"from\": 2236, \"to\": 2245}, {\"ngram\": \"the last rider\", \"from\": 2257, \"to\": 2271}, {\"ngram\": \"the finale\", \"from\": 2345, \"to\": 2355}, {\"ngram\": \"the race\", \"from\": 2359, \"to\": 2367}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Tom Pidcock, who won mountain bike gold for Britain this week, finished 13th, crossing the line alongside the world champion V