: 3793, \"to\": 3811}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But he soon let up and Healy and Lutsenko were allowed to stay 40 seconds clear.\", \"from\": 3813, \"to\": 3893, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Healy\", \"from\": 3836, \"to\": 3841}, {\"ngram\": \"Lutsenko\", \"from\": 3846, \"to\": 3854}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Then came a key move.\", \"from\": 3895, \"to\": 3916, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a key move\", \"from\": 3905, \"to\": 3915}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Madous and a few others - Fred Wright (Great Britain), Michael Woods (Canada), Nils Politt (Germany), Stefan Kung (Switzerland) and Marco Haller (Austria) - raced away from the main bunch and caught up with Healy and Lutsenko while Evenepoel and Belgian teammate Wout van Aert missed the moment, as did Dutchman Van der Poel.\", \"from\": 3917, \"to\": 4242, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3943, \"end\": 3954, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Wright_(cyclist)\", \"score\": 0.9999956969842781, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Fred Wright\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Wright_(cyclist)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Wright_(cyclist)\"}, {\"begin\": 3956, \"end\": 3969, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.9996889662220507, \"rank\": 0.00031043769453351164, \"text\": \"Great Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}, {\"begin\": 3972, \"end\": 3985, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Woods_(DJ)\", \"score\": 0.6748750082199441, \"rank\": 0.33912275537233105, \"text\": \"Michael Woods\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Woods_(DJ)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Woods_(DJ)\"}, {\"begin\": 3987, \"end\": 3993, \"title\": \"http://dbp